          <text><![CDATA[<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal"><strong>Closing the Digital Divide for Students Act of 2015</strong></p> <p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal">Amends the United States Housing Act of 1937 to require high-speed Internet service costs to be included in public housing utility allowances for households with children who qualify for free and reduced price school lunches. </p> <p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt" class="MsoNormal">Prohibits a dwelling unit's Internet cost allowance from: (1) exceeding the lowest cost available in the area, and (2) including costs for cable or satellite television or for joint packages for Internet service together with cable or satellite television. </p> <p>Conditions Internet cost allowances on the service including technology to block visual depictions that are obscene or harmful to minors. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-05-15T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
